instructions:
You can roll skills directly from the sheet, by clicking on the corresponding name or the roll button at the beginning of the row. Please contact Michael R. for any questions.
An example macro to roll hit and dmg in the same roll for first melee weapon:

 &{template:dh2ed}
[[[[floor((@{WeaponSkill}+ ?{Aim | No aim (+0),+0 | Half aim (+10),+10 | Full aim (+20),+20} + ?{Attack Type | All out (+30),+30| Charge (+20),+20 |Standard (+10),+10 | Swift Attack (+0),+0 | Lighting (-10),-10} + [[?{Modifier|+0}]])/10))]]-[[floor([[1d100cs<1cf>100]]/10)]]]]
 {{name=@{repeating_meleeweapons_$0_meleeweaponname}}}
{{roll= $[[2]] }}
{{degrees=$[[4]]}}
{{skill=@{WeaponSkill}}}
{{aim=?{Aim | No aim (+0),+0 | Half aim (+10),+10 | Full aim (+20),+20} }}
{{attacktype= ?{Attack Type | All out (+30),+30 Allout| Charge (+20),+20 |Standard (+10),+10 | Swift Attack (+0),0 | Lighting (-10),-10}}}
 {{modifier=?{Modifier|+0} }}
 {{target=[[@{WeaponSkill}+ [[?{Aim | No aim (+0),0 | Half aim (+10),10 | Full aim (+20),20} + ?{Attack Type | All out (+30),30| Charge (+20),20 |Standard (+10),10 | Swift Attack (+0),0 | Lighting (-10),-10} + [[?{Modifier|0}]]]]]]}}
{{damage=[[@{repeating_meleeweapons_$0_meleeweapondamage}+@{UnS}+floor(@{strength}/10)]]}}
 {{damagetype=@{repeating_meleeweapons_$0_meleeweapontype}}}
 {{special=@{repeating_meleeweapons_$0_meleeweaponspecial}}}
 {{penetration= @{repeating_meleeweapons_$0_meleeweaponpen}}}
